title: Mushroom (disambiguation)
content:
The RuneScape Wiki also has an article on: rsw:Mushroom

Mushroom may refer to:

  • Mushroom, a bittercap mushroom grown with the Farming skill
    • Mushroom spore, spores used to grow bittercap mushrooms
  • Mushroom (mountain troll), a troll
  • Mushrooms, a food item found within Dorgesh-Kaan
  • Mushroom & onion, a cooking ingredient made by combining fried mushrooms and fried onions
  • Mushroom Forest, a region on Fossil Island
  • Mushroom patch, a farming patch located west of Canifis
  • Mushroom pie, a pie made with a sulliuscep cap using the Cooking skill
    • Uncooked mushroom pie
  • Mushroom potato, a food item made by combining mushroom & onion and a potato with butter
  • Black mushroom, a quest item using during Shadow of the Storm and The Golem
    • Black dye, made from a black mushroom
  • Fairy ring, a ring of mushrooms used for transportation
  • Fossilised mushroom, a fossil that can be obtained by cleaning an unidentified large fossil
  • Mort myre fungus, a mushroom found within Mort Myre Swamp, used in Herblore
  • Mutated Zygomite, a monster resembling a mushroom
    • Ancient Zygomite, a stronger variant of a Mutated Zygomite
  • Mycelium pool, a pool thriving with mushrooms, used to turn fossils into enriched bones
  • Mycelium Transportation System, a transportation system using magic mushroom trees
  • Sliced mushrooms, a cooking ingredient made by using a bowl with a mushroom
    • Fried mushrooms, cooked sliced mushrooms
    • Burnt mushroom, burnt sliced mushrooms
  • Stinkhorn mushroom, an item found within the Chambers of Xeric
  • Sulliuscep, a type of mushroom grown on Fossil Island
    • Sulliuscep cap, an item that can be obtained from harvesting sulliusceps
 This page is used to distinguish between articles with similar names.
If an internal link led you to this disambiguation page, you may wish to change the link to point directly to the intended article.
